==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tropaeolin
<hw>Tro*pae"o*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A name given to any one of a series of orange-red dyestuffs
produced artificially from certain complex sulphonic acid derivatives of
azo and diazo hydrocarbons of the aromatic series; -- so called because
of the general resemblance to the shades of nasturtium
(<gen>Tropaeolum</gen>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trope</ent>⟦br⟧
